      • checkQuestSlots

        private boolean checkQuestSlots()
        Determines the quest slot to use. If the quest isn't already running and no quest slot of the fitting type is available, false will be retuned, so the interaction can be cancelled.
        Returns:
        If a usable quest slot was found.
        See Also:
        PlayerConfigurator.getCharacterRunningMainQuest(Player)

      • checkQuestCompletion

        private boolean checkQuestCompletion()
        Determines if the quest cannot be repeated right now. If the quest is daily and has a cooldown, the remaining time, till the quest is redoable is shown. If the quest is not daily and already complete, a completion message is shown.
        Returns:
        If the quest cannot be repeated right now.
        See Also:
        PlayerQuestConfigurator.getQuestCooldown(Player, String), PlayerQuestConfigurator.isQuestCompleted(Player, String), WauzQuest.getCompletedDialog()

      • checkQuestObjectives

        private boolean checkQuestObjectives()
        Determines if all objectives of the quest phase are fulfilled. If the quest is running and phase requirements are not met, an "uncomplete" message is shown.
        Returns:
        If all quest objectives are fulfilled.
        See Also:
        QuestRequirementChecker.checkRequirements(), WauzQuest.getUncompletedMessage(int)

      • acceptQuest

        private void acceptQuest()
        Lets the player accept the quest. If the quest is unstarted, an accept dialog is shown, or accepted directly, if it is a main quest.
        See Also:
        WauzPlayerEventQuestAccept

      • completeQuestStep

        private void completeQuestStep()
        Starts the next quest phase or completes the quest. If the phase is completed, the next phase is initiated and an phase description message is shown. If all phases are completed, the reward chooser dialog is opened.
        See Also:
        WauzQuest.getPhaseDialog(int), PlayerQuestConfigurator.setQuestPhase(Player, String, int), QuestRewardChooser.open(Player, WauzQuest, WauzPlayerEventQuestComplete)
